guess he always was) is he campable?<br>
<br>
what happens if multible people are waiting for him to pop, does one have rights over the other?<br>
<br>
I already have an opinion on the matter but I was wondering how the actually people that need ragefire will handle it.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uroatusbh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RoatusBH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/6/01 11:16:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: question about ragefire</span><hr size=1> It's campable.<br>
<br>
If there is a cleric(or his mule on 2nd puter) who is sitting in naggy lair,<br>
he has right to take Ragefire when it pops.<br>
Anyone else who come later shouldn't touch it.<br>
<br>
This DOESN'T count FDing monk waiting for ragefire<br>
in the full spawns of FGs btw.<br>
<br>
Roatus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uveldanlionsfury.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veldan Lionsfury</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 149<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/6/01 11:33:09 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: question about ragefire</span><hr size=1> Why not? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utorquill.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Torquill</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://forums.interealms.com/ranger/images/icons/Eeeeek_Face_2.gif HEIGHT =15 WIDTH=15 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 178<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/6/01 1:34:27 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.flspot.com/loa/mb/icons/ico_torquill.gif Height=84 Width=75></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: question about ragefire</span><hr size=1> FCFS mean the first cleric to show up with a force to take out Ragefire get him, if I understand correctly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukraghack.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kraghack</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 754<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/6/01 1:58:48 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: question about ragefire</span><hr size=1> <br>
Sorry, if I'm feigned in the lair I have just as much claim to a camp as someone sitting in an empty room. <p>Bahd - Level 57 monk<BR>
Gott - Level 52 druid<BR>
Member of Watchers, Brell Serilis
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukestrithebard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KestriTheBard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FFFF66>Board Moderator  <br><font color=#A0B0E0>&lt;Clan Spiritslammer&gt;  </font></span><br>  Posts: 621<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/7/01 7:31:34 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: question about ragefire</span><hr size=1> No what they are saying is that you can't just sit there and claim him unless you are able to kill him.  If you have a force on hand ready to kill him you can claim him.  But if you are alone and another person comes up with the force ready to take him you should bow out and try again another day.<br>
<br>
 <p><center>
<img src="http://home.kscable.com/sadara/images/Sigs/kestri.gif"></center>
<center>Kestri the Bard, proud to support meleers and casters everywhere<br>
Loving Daughter to Chants<br>
Recruiting officer for Clan Spiritslammer<br>
</center>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufettenmysteblayde.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fetten Mysteblayde</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 138<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/8/01 5:16:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: question about ragefire</span><hr size=1> That isn't always the case with VS/VSR in Karnor's....<br>
Go into Karnor's every so often and ask for a camp check. I'll bet ya see nearly every time someone camping VS/VSR. Nearly everytime it's by one or 2 people just waiting to pop and when he does they call in all the people to do it. When he does pop the response changes from camped to claimed while they gather the people they need. Since it's gone that way I've only seen one camper bow out to an on the spot raid ready group. I'm not saying that is the only time it has happened I'm sure it has happened other times as well.<br>
<br>
Oh, btw why does Ragfire have to be camped by a cleric or a cleric's mule?? Is that a new provision that I missed? I have guild clerics that my guild would benefit amazingly by having a rez stick or 2. Shouldn't I be able to take out time as a guild leader to camp Ragefire if he is fcfs? I mean after all it benefits my guild, any raid that my guild clerics attend and me personally (I am a ranger after all).<br>
<br>
If Ragefire is fcfs and you want to camp it whether your a cleric or not, to benefit yourself/guild/friends and can get the people there when he spawns go ahead it's your time your giving up to do so. However, I do think if it is going to take awhile to get those people ready and there is a ready crew there you should bow out and let them have it. That way you have a pretty clear cut idea when the next one is going to be up and have a crew there ready to go in and take him down when he pops.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ushamibuushkaforestfury.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shamibuushka Forestfury</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 506<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/8/01 5:24:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: question about ragefire</span><hr size=1> you cant just claim it by sitting in lair, if its fcfs just get your raid there first and kill it.  <br>
<br>
edit : same with VS, its hilarious when people try to claim it from zone, just get your raid there and kill it. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ushamibuushkaforestfury.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shamibuushka Forestfury</A> at: 6/8/01 5:26:27 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzestrenocya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zestrenocya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FFFF66>Hero of Brell Serilis <img src=http://www.brellserilis.net/images/goldstartr.gif align=middle><br><font color=#A0B0E0>&lt;Silent Redemption&gt; </font></span><br>  Posts: 1324<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/9/01 6:28:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: question about ragefire</span><hr size=1> If you're there first with your raid, you can kill it.<br>
<br>
